data-triple-N3.o: "A penalty kick (also known as penalty or spot kick) is a type of direct free kick in association football, taken from 12 yards (approximately 11 metres) out from the goal. Penalty kicks are performed during normal play. They are awarded when a player commits a foul inside their own penalty area."@en
